Spontaneous regression of cardiomyopathy in a patient with the acquired immunodeficiency syndrome.
 Cardiac involvement is common in patients with the acquired immunodeficiency syndrome (AIDS) and, when symptomatic, it portends a poor prognosis.
 We present a case of marked spontaneous regression of cardiomyopathy in a patient with AIDS.
 To our knowledge, this is the first reported case of spontaneous recovery of ventricular function in an AIDS patient.
